.Dd April 7, 2026
.Dt MANEATER.TOML 5
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm maneater.toml
.Nd configuration file for maneater
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
is the configuration file for
.Xr maneater 1 .
It uses TOML format and controls model selection, embedding prefixes,
shell command permissions, and session namespacing.
.Sh FILE HIERARCHY
Configuration files are loaded and merged in order:
.Bl -enum
.It
.Pa ~/.config/maneater/maneater.toml
(global).
Falls back to
.Pa ~/.config/maneater/models.toml
if the primary file does not exist.
.It
Each parent directory between
.Ev HOME
and the current working directory.
.It
.Pa ./maneater.toml
(project-local).
.El
.Pp
Later files override earlier ones.
Models are merged by name; keys from the overlay replace keys in the base,
while unset keys are preserved.
Manpath include lists and exec rules accumulate: both are appended across
hierarchy levels.
The
.Va manpath.no-auto
and
.Va exec.session
fields are replaced entirely if present in an overlay.
.Sh TOP-LEVEL KEYS
.Bl -tag -width "default"
.It Va default
Name of the default model.
Must match a key in the
.Va models
table.
Required when multiple models are configured; optional when only one
model exists (that model is used automatically).
.El
.Sh MODELS
Each model is a sub-table under
.Va models
keyed by an arbitrary name.
.Bl -tag -width "document-prefix"
.It Va path
Absolute path to a GGUF model file.
Supports
.Ev $VAR
and
.Ev ${VAR}
environment variable expansion.
Required.
.It Va query-prefix
String prepended to queries before embedding.
Used for asymmetric search models.
Optional.
.It Va document-prefix
String prepended to documents before embedding.
Optional.
.El
.Pp
Example:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
default = "nomic"

[models.nomic]
path = "${MANEATER_MODEL_PATH}"
query-prefix = "search_query: "
document-prefix = "search_document: "
.Ed
.Sh MANPATH
The
.Va manpath
table controls how
.Nm maneater
discovers man pages beyond the system
.Xr manpath 1 .
.Pp
By default,
.Nm maneater
probes the current working directory for common in-repo man page locations:
.Pp
.Bl -bullet -compact
.It
.Pa man/
.It
.Pa doc/man/
.It
.Pa share/man/
.El
.Pp
Directories that exist are prepended to the system manpath, so project pages
shadow system pages with the same name.
.Bl -tag -width "include"
.It Va include
Array of additional directories to prepend to the manpath.
Relative paths are resolved from the current working directory.
Supports
.Ev $VAR
and
.Ev ${VAR}
environment variable expansion.
Include lists accumulate across hierarchy levels.
.It Va no-auto
When set to
.Cm true ,
disables heuristic probing of
.Pa man/ ,
.Pa doc/man/ ,
and
.Pa share/man/ .
Only explicit
.Va include
paths and the system manpath are used.
Default:
.Cm false .
.El
.Pp
Example:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
[manpath]
include = ["vendor/man", "${PROJECT_ROOT}/result/share/man"]
.Ed
.Pp
To disable heuristic probing in a project:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
[manpath]
no-auto = true
.Ed
.Sh EXEC
The
.Va exec
table controls which shell commands the
.Cm exec
tool is allowed to run.
.Pp
By default, no commands are permitted.
The
.Cm exec
tool denies all commands until explicit allow rules are configured.
This applies regardless of whether the
.Va exec
table is present: a missing table, an empty table, and a table with
only deny rules all result in every command being denied.
.Ss Permission rules
Rules are defined as arrays of tables under
.Va exec.allow
and
.Va exec.deny .
Each rule has the following fields:
.Bl -tag -width "binary"
.It Va binary
Basename of the executable to match (e.g.,
.Dq git ,
not
.Dq /usr/bin/git ) .
Required.
.It Va args
Array of argument-prefix patterns.
Each pattern is split on whitespace and matched as a prefix against the
command's arguments.
If empty or omitted, no argument filtering is applied.
.It Va cwd
Array of glob patterns that must match the working directory.
Uses
.Xr filepath.Match 3
syntax
.Pq Li * , Li ? , Li [...] .
If empty or omitted, no directory restriction is applied.
.It Va env
Map of environment variables injected into the executed command.
Only applied to matching allow rules; deny rules do not inject variables.
.El
.Ss Evaluation order
.Bl -enum
.It
If any deny rule matches, the command is denied regardless of allow rules.
.It
The command must match at least one allow rule.
If no allow rules exist, all commands are denied.
.It
Within a rule, all non-empty fields must match (AND logic).
.El
.Pp
Example:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
[[exec.allow]]
binary = "git"
args = ["status", "diff", "log"]
cwd = ["/home/*/repos/*"]
env = { GIT_AUTHOR_NAME = "bot" }

[[exec.allow]]
binary = "jq"

[[exec.deny]]
binary = "git"
args = ["push --force"]

[[exec.deny]]
binary = "sudo"
.Ed
.Ss Session namespacing
The
.Va exec.session
sub-table controls how cached exec result URIs are namespaced.
.Bl -tag -width "fallback"
.It Va env
Name of the environment variable used to determine the session bucket.
Default:
.Dq CLAUDE_SESSION_ID .
.It Va fallback
Value used when the environment variable is unset or empty.
Default:
.Dq no-session .
.El
.Pp
Session strings are sanitized to
.Li [A-Za-z0-9._-]
only.
.Pp
Example:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
[exec.session]
env = "MY_SESSION_ID"
fallback = "default"
.Ed
.Sh EXAMPLES
Minimal configuration with a single model:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
[models.nomic]
path = "/opt/models/nomic-embed-text-v1.5.Q8_0.gguf"
.Ed
.Pp
Project-local configuration restricting exec to read-only git commands:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
[[exec.allow]]
binary = "git"
args = ["status", "diff", "log", "show", "blame"]

[[exec.deny]]
binary = "git"
args = ["push", "reset", "checkout"]
.Ed
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr maneater 1 ,
.Xr moxy 1 ,
.Xr toml 5
